TOPICS COVERED (DATA PREPROCESSING & FEATURE ENGINEERING FOR MACHINE LEARNING)
Introduction to Data Preprocessing

The training session began with an introduction to Data Preprocessing, one of the most important phases in the Machine Learning lifecycle. Learned that real-world datasets are often incomplete, inconsistent, and noisy, making them unsuitable for directly training Machine Learning models. The trainer explained that preprocessing improves the quality of data, resulting in better model accuracy and performance.

Discussed the complete data preprocessing pipeline, including data cleaning, handling missing values, removing duplicates, detecting outliers, encoding categorical variables, scaling numerical features, and feature engineering.

Understanding Real-World Datasets

Explored different real-world datasets containing missing values, duplicate records, inconsistent data types, and incorrect entries.

Learned how poor-quality data can lead to:

Low prediction accuracy
Biased Machine Learning models
Incorrect analysis
Overfitting and underfitting problems

Discussed the importance of validating data before starting model training.

Handling Missing Values

Studied different techniques for identifying and handling missing data using the Pandas library.

Practiced:

Detecting missing values using isnull()
Counting missing values using sum()
Displaying percentage of missing data
Filling missing values using:
Mean
Median
Mode
Constant values
Removing missing records using dropna()

Compared different strategies and discussed when each method should be applied.

