Feature Scaling

Learned why numerical features with different scales affect Machine Learning algorithms.

Studied two important scaling techniques:

Normalization (Min-Max Scaling)

Converts values into the range of 0 to 1.

Standardization (Z-Score Scaling)

Converts values to have zero mean and unit variance.

Discussed which Machine Learning algorithms require feature scaling and why it improves model performance.

